const title = "ILVE Range & Appliance Repair Los Angeles — Same Day";
const description = "ILVE range, oven & cooktop repair in LA. Same-day service, OEM parts. Italian dual-fuel specialists. $89 diagnostic, waived with repair.";

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "What ILVE appliances do you repair in Los Angeles?",
    a: "ILVE's full US lineup — primarily ranges, with cooktops and wall ovens secondary. The Majestic and Nostalgie collections dominate our LA service mix. Majestic II Series ranges (UMTFI / UPTFI variants in 60cm / 76cm / 90cm / 100cm / 120cm widths). Nostalgie series (UPI / UPDN variants with the distinctive vintage-style chrome trim and curved enamel front). Professional Plus series. Induction ranges (UMDI / UPDI variants). Built-in wall ovens (660 series). Standalone cooktops (90cm and 60cm gas, induction). The 90cm dual-fuel range is the dominant configuration in our LA mix — UMTFI90 and similar variants — chosen by Bel Air, Beverly Hills, and Hancock Park kitchens specifically because they wanted something that looked Italian rather than industrial. ILVE doesn't make refrigerators, dishwashers, or laundry — kitchens with an ILVE range typically pair it with Sub-Zero, Miele, or Bosch for the other categories."
  },
  {
    q: "How much does ILVE repair cost in LA?",
    a: "Diagnostic is $89, applied toward the repair when you approve the work. ILVE pricing sits in the upper-luxury tier with a parts-cost premium for Italian-origin supply. Common ILVE service items: ceramic igniter $185-$285 per zone; gas burner spark module $265-$405; oven thermostat $285-$425; bake / broil element $265-$385; convection fan motor $345-$525; oven door gasket $185-$285 (the 2015-2020 Nostalgie cohort failure — see year-pattern below); door hinge $345-$525; enamel front panel coordination (variable by color and size, $485-$1,400, plus 14-21 day Italian shipping lead); main control board $385-$580; gas valve assembly $345-$525; induction generator board on UMDI / UPDI variants $485-$780 (induction electronics carry a higher parts cost than standard gas-burner controls). Parts ship from Italy via ILVE's US distribution — 14-21 day typical lead is the longest of any brand we service, longer than Bertazzoni or Smeg, and worth setting expectations on at diagnostic so the customer can plan around the repair timeline."
  },
  {
    q: "Why do ILVE parts take so long to arrive?",
    a: "ILVE parts ship from Campodarsego, Padova — the family factory in northeast Italy where every range and oven is built and stocked. There's a US distribution network in place (ILVE USA), but for non-stocked components the parts route is: order from US distribution → US distribution orders from Italy → ocean freight or air freight to US → US distribution to our truck. Even with air freight on critical components, the supply chain runs 14-21 days end-to-end. Common wear items (ceramic igniters, spark modules, door gaskets) are sometimes stocked in US distribution and can ship in 5-10 days. Less-common parts and color-specific panel components routinely run the full 14-21 days. We diagnose, quote, and document the lead time upfront — and on Nostalgie or custom-color installations specifically, the repair-vs-replace math always favors repair regardless of timeline, since custom enamel colors aren't always available for replacement-unit purchase either."
  },
  {
    q: "Can you match my ILVE enamel color if a panel needs replacement?",
    a: "Sometimes — and this is one of the distinctive realities of working on ILVE. The brand offers 200+ standard enamel colors plus custom color matching on order, which means the exact finish on your range may have been a specific color spec chosen during the original purchase. <strong>If your color is still in ILVE's current catalog</strong>, panel replacement is a coordination job through ILVE USA: identify the color code from the spec plate (usually printed on a sticker inside the lower front panel; sometimes only available from the original dealer), order through ILVE USA, 14-28 day Italian shipping lead. Cost varies by panel size: 60cm panels $485-$680, 76cm $585-$880, 90cm $680-$1,080, 100cm and 120cm $880-$1,400. <strong>If your color was a limited-run or custom finish that's been discontinued</strong>, panel replacement may not be available — Italian factory archives don't always retain discontinued color formulas. In those cases, repair (rather than replacement) is the only path to keep the kitchen aesthetic intact. ILVE owners with custom colors are exactly the customers for whom the repair-vs-replace math always favors repair, and that's how we frame every diagnostic on a custom-finish installation."
  },
  {
    q: "How long do ILVE appliances last?",
    a: "ILVE ranges are designed for 25-30 year service life with normal use — among the longest projected lifespans of any range brand we service. The construction philosophy is heavy-duty Italian commercial-derived: cast iron grates, heavy steel construction, brass valves, hand-painted enamel that's repaintable if necessary. The components that wear are predictable: ceramic igniters year 5-8 ($185-$285 per zone), spark modules year 4-6 ($265-$405), oven door gasket year 6-8 in high-use LA kitchens ($185-$285 — see year-pattern callout for the 2015-2020 Nostalgie pattern), oven thermostat year 7-10 ($285-$425), convection fan motor year 10-14 ($345-$525), main control board year 12-18 ($385-$580). Heavy-use households (multiple cooking sessions daily, restaurant-style) compress these windows by 2-3 years. Replacement-unit pricing: Majestic II 76cm starts around $7,500, 90cm around $9,500, 120cm dual-fuel professional approaches $18,000, Nostalgie series carries a $2,000-$4,000 design premium over equivalent Majestic. Against those numbers, $400-$800 mid-life repair recovers another 8-12 years of service. We've worked on ILVE ranges 20+ years old still operating cleanly with no major surgery."
  },
  {
    q: "How does ILVE compare to Bertazzoni?",
    a: "Both are Italian heritage brands and the comparison comes up frequently because they share showroom space and the same target customer (LA owners wanting an Italian range). Honest differences from servicing both regularly: <strong>ILVE</strong> is family-owned (Campodarsego, Padova) since 1952, hand-painted enamel finish, dual-fuel configuration standard, 200+ color options, Nostalgie vintage-style and Majestic professional collections. <strong>Bertazzoni</strong> is family-owned (Guastalla, Reggio Emilia) since 1882, three distinct collections (Master, Professional, Heritage) with different parts ecosystems, color options across the same range plus custom panel program, ThermalFlow vs Multiflow convection technology by collection. The build quality is comparable — both 25-30 year service life targets, both heavy steel construction. ILVE leans more toward design statement (the Nostalgie collection particularly is unmistakably ILVE). Bertazzoni leans more toward range-of-options across price tiers (Heritage entry, Professional mid, Master flagship). Parts pricing runs comparable in the standard wear-item band; ILVE color-panel coordination tends to be slightly more expensive than Bertazzoni's. Lead times are similar on Italian-origin parts. The choice between them in a Bel Air or Beverly Hills installation is usually aesthetic rather than technical."
  },
  {
    q: "Where can I find the official ILVE manual or warranty information?",
    a: `For official ILVE documentation, warranty registration, and authorized service locator, visit <a href="https://www.ilveusa.com/support/" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">ILVE USA official support &amp; manuals</a>. Our technicians work independently of ILVE's factory service network — we're often faster and available same-day across Southern California.`
  }
];

