<!-- 01 INTRO -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">01, About this service</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">ILVE is the most Italian range you can buy — Campodarsego, Padova since 1952, hand-painted enamel, dual-fuel only — we see them in Bel Air and Beverly Hills kitchens where the owner wanted something that looks like it belongs in a Venetian palazzo.</h2>

    <p>ILVE is manufactured by ILVE S.r.l. in Campodarsego, a small town in the Padova province of the Veneto region in northeast Italy. The company has been family-owned since founding in 1952 and still operates from the same factory. Every ILVE range and oven is built and finished in Campodarsego — the hand-painted enamel exterior is applied at the factory by craftsmen, and the 200+ standard colors plus custom finish program means each range has the option of being specified with a finish unique to that kitchen. In our 5-county SoCal service area, ILVE shows up in a specific demographic: Bel Air, Beverly Hills, Holmby Hills, and Hancock Park kitchens where the owner specifically wanted an Italian range with vintage-style design (the Nostalgie collection particularly) or where the kitchen was designed around a specific custom enamel color match.</p>

    <p>Three ILVE-specific realities shape every service call. First, <strong>dual-fuel configuration is standard across the range lineup</strong> — gas burner cooktop, electric convection oven, the configuration most luxury cooks prefer for the precise oven temperature control electric provides. Service implications: gas-side wear items (ceramic igniters, spark modules, gas valves) coexist with electric-side items (bake / broil element, oven thermostat, convection fan), and the diagnostic tree has to account for both. Second, <strong>parts ship from Italy via the ILVE USA distribution network</strong>, with 14-21 day typical lead time — the longest of any brand we service, longer than Bertazzoni or Smeg. Common wear items (igniters, gaskets) are sometimes stocked in US distribution and can ship in 5-10 days; less-common parts and color-specific panel components routinely run the full 14-21 days. We document lead times upfront so customers can plan around the timeline. Third, <strong>200+ colors plus custom finish means panel coordination is a brand-specific service category</strong>. When a panel needs replacement, color matching is a coordination job through ILVE USA back to the Campodarsego factory, and on discontinued custom colors the answer can be "repair is the only path." That reality shapes how we frame repair-vs-replace math on every ILVE diagnostic.</p>

    <p>This page covers ILVE repair across the US lineup — Majestic II Series ranges, Nostalgie series with vintage-style chrome trim, Professional Plus, induction variants (UMDI / UPDI), built-in wall ovens (660 series), and standalone cooktops. Every ILVE service call gets a $89 residential diagnostic (applied toward the repair when work is approved), OEM ILVE parts, and an honest written quote before any work begins.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 02 CATEGORIES -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">02, ILVE service categories</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Ranges, cooktops, wall ovens — the Italian heritage service tree.</h2>

    <div class="callout-box">
      <h3>2015-2020 Nostalgie series oven door gasket pattern (most common ILVE service call in LA)</h3>
      <p>The Nostalgie series ranges manufactured between roughly 2015 and 2020 develop oven door gasket deterioration around year 6 to 8 in high-use LA kitchens (lower if the household is restaurant-style daily cooking, longer if the range is moderate-use). The early sign is small enamel paint chips visible near the hinge side of the oven door — the gasket compression cycle stresses the enamel at the hinge corners as the seal hardens with age, and the chipping precedes the gasket failure itself by 6-12 months. By the time most owners call us with the symptom (oven heating slowly, temperature uneven, smell of escaping gas during preheat), the gasket is fully compromised. Fix is oven door gasket replacement with OEM ILVE part ($185-$285 with labor). Same-day when we stock the common Nostalgie gasket on the truck. <strong>Worth scheduling proactively at year 6-7</strong> on Nostalgie owners who haven't yet shown the symptom — preventive replacement is cheaper than the matched-pattern enamel touch-up that becomes necessary if chipping has spread.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="appliance-grid">
      <div class="appliance-card">
        <h3>Majestic II Series ranges</h3>
        <p>60cm / 76cm / 90cm / 100cm / 120cm widths, dual-fuel configuration (gas cooktop, electric convection oven). Standard wear tree: ceramic igniters ($185-$285 per zone), spark modules ($265-$405), oven thermostat ($285-$425), convection fan motor ($345-$525), bake / broil element ($265-$385).</p>
      </div>
      <div class="appliance-card">
        <h3>Nostalgie series ranges</h3>
        <p>Vintage-style design with chrome trim and curved enamel front. Same dual-fuel platform as Majestic II underneath; distinctive aesthetic shell on top. Service tree overlaps with Majestic II; Nostalgie-specific items are the trim hardware and the door gasket pattern (above).</p>
      </div>
      <div class="appliance-card">
        <h3>Professional Plus</h3>
        <p>Upper-tier specification within the Majestic II platform — heavier brass valves, higher BTU burners, distinct trim. Service tree shares 90% with standard Majestic; some Professional-specific part numbers on the burner valves and igniters.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="appliance-card">
        <h3>Induction ranges (UMDI / UPDI)</h3>
        <p>Induction cooktop variants paired with electric convection oven. Different cooktop diagnostic — induction generator boards ($485-$780), cooktop glass replacement ($585-$985), induction coil service. Higher parts cost than gas-burner platforms, faster diagnostic on cooktop side once symptoms are isolated.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="appliance-card">
        <h3>Built-in wall ovens (660 series)</h3>
        <p>60cm and 76cm built-in wall ovens with the same convection and electric oven hardware as the range platform. Bake / broil element, oven thermostat, convection fan, control board, door hinge service. Standard wall-oven service tree with ILVE Italian-origin parts.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="appliance-card">
        <h3>Standalone cooktops</h3>
        <p>60cm and 90cm gas and induction cooktops. Smaller footprint of the range cooktop side. Same burner architecture, same service tree, no oven cavity in play.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

