<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">04, Recent repairs</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">ILVE jobs from across the territory.</h2>

    <div class="repair-grid">
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>ILVE Nostalgie UPI90FE 90cm range, Beverly Hills</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> Oven slow to preheat, temperature reading 25°F low compared to thermometer, faint gas smell during preheat phase. Unit was 7 years old, 2018 Nostalgie cohort. Owner had noticed enamel chipping near the hinge for several months without connecting it to the oven symptom.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Classic 2015-2020 Nostalgie oven door gasket deterioration pattern. Gasket fully compromised, gas escaping during preheat (hence the smell), heat loss explained the slow preheat and temperature reading. Enamel chipping near hinge was the visual early sign that had preceded the gasket failure.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> Oven door gasket replacement with OEM ILVE part (in stock in US distribution, 6-day arrival). Verified clean seal and accurate preheat after installation. Recommended preventive enamel touch-up to address the chipping.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost & time:</strong> $265 total. Two visits — diagnostic + part arrival.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>ILVE Majestic UMTFI90 90cm dual-fuel, Bel Air</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> Convection mode producing uneven bake — front of pan well-cooked, back undercooked. Standard bake mode worked normally. Unit was 11 years old, well past convection fan motor service window.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Convection fan motor running at significantly reduced RPM — year 11 unit, bearing wear consistent with normal service curve. Oven thermostat and elements within spec.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> Convection fan motor replacement with OEM ILVE part. Verified even bake on test cycle in both convection and standard modes.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost & time:</strong> $485 total. Two visits — diagnostic + 12-day parts arrival from Italy.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>ILVE UMDI90 induction range, Hancock Park</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> Front-right induction zone not heating despite cookware-detected indicator showing pan present. Other three zones working normally. Unit was 6 years old.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Induction generator board zone-1 channel failed. Coil tested within spec, cookware detection working — the generator output stage for that specific zone had failed. Other channels on the same board reading clean.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> Induction generator board replacement with OEM ILVE part. Verified all four zones operating at full power range. Cookware-detection working across the board.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost & time:</strong> $785 total. Two visits — diagnostic + 16-day parts arrival from Italy.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

